    "outOfScopeRationale": "Root cause adequacy cannot be inferred from the RCA document alone; the bundle lacks expert review validating that the identified cause is the underlying cause rather than a proximate symptom.",
    "evidenceGapDescription": "The bundle contains: nonconformity record (description, closure date), root cause analysis attributing staleness to TTL misconfig. The bundle does NOT contain: independent expert review of the RCA itself confirming that TTL misconfig is the underlying root cause (not just the proximate trigger). The OOS verdict signals to the auditor that the client should provide expert RCA review before clause 10.2.b.2 adequacy can be evaluated."
